There has been an increase in murders in South Africa. This is according to the latest crime statistics released by Police Minister Bheki Cele. The results reflect a three-month period at the end of 2021. eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - South Africa's murder rate is escalating out of control. The latest crime statistics show an increase of 8.9 percent from October to December last year. And while the country grapples with serious crimes, tension between the Police Minister and the national police commissioner appears to be the last thing the SAPS needs now. READ: Crime stats | Cele says murder remains 'worryingly stubborn' A total of 6,859 people were murdered between October and December, with the murder rate going up for a fifth consecutive year. While attempted murders and car hijackings are also on the rise, gender-based violence remains the police's top priority. * eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports.